05. Explain the LLD

This is my Parking Lot design.
ParkingLot is the main class and has many Floors (composition).
Each Floor contains many ParkingSpots.
ParkingSpot knows its type (Car, Bike, Truck) and whether it's occupied.
Vehicle has license plate and type.
Ticket links a Vehicle to a ParkingSpot with entry time.
Payment is linked to a Ticket with amount and status.Main operations:
parkVehicle: Find available spot of matching type → create Ticket → mark spot occupied.
exitVehicle: Use ticketId to find spot → calculate time → create Payment → free the spot.

06. Explain Trade-offs

Used composition (ParkingLot has Floors) instead of inheritance because floors are parts of the lot.
Used enums for VehicleType to avoid magic strings.
For scalability, I could add multiple entry gates later by adding a Gate class.
Payment calculation is simple — could be extended to hourly rates.

