Some possible queries :

Why we did not use Inheritance for Vehicles like Car extends Vehicle, Truck extends Vehicle ?

We used Composition (ParkingSpot has a Vehicle)
instead of Inheritance (Car extends Vehicle) for the following reasons:

1. "Is-A" vs "Has-A" Relationship

Inheritance (Car extends Vehicle) means:
Car IS-A Vehicle — This is true in real life.

But in the Parking Lot system, the core relationship is:
ParkingSpot HAS-A Vehicle (a spot is occupied by a vehicle)

Using inheritance here would be incorrect modeling because:

A ParkingSpot is not a type of Vehicle
A Vehicle is not a type of ParkingSpot

So we use Composition: ParkingSpot contains (has) a Vehicle.

